name: Physically active children, United Kingdom, 2007/08
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on physical activity provision for school children.  By highlighting areas with low participation rates in order to assess need and enable targeted intervention. The percentage of children attending state schools belonging to a School Sport Partnership who participate in at least 2 hours of high quality PE and school sport within and beyond the curriculum in a typical week of the academic year.
